# drop nulls that are irrelevant
def nullDrop(gData):
    gData.dropna(subset = ["Date_Mscan","Date_LTZ"],inplace = True)
    gData.drop('Source_ID', axis = 1, inplace = True)
    return gData

#show all data that has a large gap in frequency of values

def graphhist(data):
    numerics = ['int16', 'int32', 'int64', 'float16', 'float32', 'float64']

    newdf = pd.DataFrame(data.select_dtypes(include=numerics)).iloc[:,3:]
    newdf["geometryX"] = data.loc[:,"geometry"].x.copy()
    newdf["geometryY"] = data.loc[:,"geometry"].y.copy()

    newdf.head()


    fig, axes = plt.subplots(3,6, figsize = (20,15))

    m = 0
    for axes in axes.flat:
        axes.hist(newdf.iloc[:,m-1])
        axes.set_title(newdf.iloc[:,m-1].name)
        m+=1
In [5]:
def cleanbyHist(gData):
    graphhist(gData)
    cleanData = gData.copy() 
    cleanData.drop(index = cleanData[cleanData.Temp_BB > 10000].index, axis = 1,inplace=True)
    cleanData.drop(index = cleanData[cleanData.Temp_BB > 10000].index, axis = 1,inplace=True)
    graphhist(cleanData)
    return cleanData

In [6]:
def limitContinents(cleanData):
    world = gpd.read_file(gpd.datasets.get_path('naturalearth_lowres'))
    #only asia + africa points
    asiaAfrica =  world.loc[(world['continent'] == "Asia") | (world['continent'] == "Africa")]
    cleanData = cleanData[cleanData.geometry.within(asiaAfrica.geometry.unary_union)] 
    cleanData.reset_index(drop = True, inplace= True)
    world = gpd.read_file(gpd.datasets.get_path('naturalearth_lowres'))
    ax = asiaAfrica.plot(figsize= (15,20),color = 'black')
    cleanData.plot(ax=ax, color = 'pink')
    plt.show()  
    return cleanData
In [19]:
#modular clustering - giving each "area" a buffer so will be assoicated by the same ID

def modularCluster(cleanData):

    spatialGroup_ID = cleanData.iloc[[0]].copy()
    spatialGroup_ID["geometry"] = spatialGroup_ID.geometry.buffer(1)
    m = 0
    spatialGroup_ID["geoID"] = m

    for index, row in cleanData.iterrows():
        geoID = None
        for index1, row1 in spatialGroup_ID.iterrows():
            if spatialGroup_ID.iloc[index1].geometry.intersects(cleanData.iloc[index].geometry):
                geoID = spatialGroup_ID.iloc[index1].geoID 
        if geoID == None:
            m += 1
            #print(f"index {index} has geoID  changed to: {m}")
            geoID = m    
        rowNew = cleanData.iloc[index].copy()
        rowNew["geometry"] = cleanData.iloc[index].geometry.buffer(1)
        rowNew["geoID"] = geoID
        spatialGroup_ID = spatialGroup_ID.append(rowNew, ignore_index = True)
    return spatialGroup_ID

def spatialDataSet(cleanData):
    world = gpd.read_file(gpd.datasets.get_path('naturalearth_lowres'))

    asiaAfrica =  world.loc[(world['continent'] == "Asia") | (world['continent'] == "Africa")]
    areasDissolve = spatialGroup_ID.dissolve(by='geoID')

    areasDissolve['geoID'] = areasDissolve.index.copy()

    ax = asiaAfrica.plot(figsize= (15,20),color = 'black')
    areasDissolve.plot(ax=ax,column = 'geoID' )
    plt.show()
